# Clean Defaults

- Preserve behavior unless the user explicitly asks for behavior changes.
- Prefer intent-revealing names for variables, functions, and types.
- Keep functions small and single-purpose; extract named helpers for orchestration.
- Use guard clauses for invalid inputs and missing runtime context.
- Prefer explicit transformations over implicit mutations.
- Keep comments minimal; explain non-obvious "why" only.
- Avoid `any`; if needed, isolate it at integration boundaries.
- When refactoring, keep or improve test coverage for decision branches and edge cases.
